<script type="application/ld+json">
{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the best business structure in India?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The best structure depends on your goals. Pvt Ltd for funding and growth. LLP for professional firms with lower compliance. OPC for solo founders. Partnership for simple small businesses. Sole proprietorship for freelancers. Consider liability protection funding needs and compliance budget."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Pvt Ltd vs LLP which is better?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Pvt Ltd is better for fundraising from VCs and has 25 percent tax rate. LLP has lower compliance and 30 percent tax but no mandatory audit below 40 lakh turnover. Pvt Ltd suits growth startups while LLP suits professional firms like CA CS and consulting businesses."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the minimum capital for Pvt Ltd?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"There is no minimum capital requirement. You can start with as low as 1 lakh authorized capital. Most startups begin with 1 lakh to minimise registration costs. Capital can be increased later as the business grows by filing with MCA and paying additional fees."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can OPC be converted to Pvt Ltd?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes mandatory conversion if turnover exceeds 2 crore or paid-up capital exceeds 50 lakh. Voluntary conversion possible anytime. The process involves passing resolution filing forms with MCA and updating MOA AOA. Takes about 15 to 30 days. Under the Companies Act 2013 Section 18 OPC conversion to Pvt Ltd requires at least two shareholders and two directors."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is unlimited liability in partnership?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Unlimited liability means partners personal assets can be used to pay business debts. If the business cannot pay creditors partners personal savings property and assets are at risk. This is the biggest disadvantage of partnership and sole proprietorship compared to Pvt Ltd and LLP."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which structure has lowest compliance?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Sole proprietorship has zero ROC compliance. Partnership has minimal filing. LLP files Form 8 and Form 11 annually. Pvt Ltd has highest compliance with annual return AGM board meetings and mandatory audit. Choose based on your willingness to invest in compliance."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which structure is best for tax saving?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Pvt Ltd at 25 percent flat rate is best for businesses with profit above 12 to 15 lakh. Below that sole proprietorship with slab rates may be better. LLP at 30 percent is higher than Pvt Ltd. Partnership also 30 percent. Consider effective rate after deductions and surcharge."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can a foreigner start a business in India?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Foreigners can be directors in Pvt Ltd and OPC. LLP requires at least one resident designated partner. Foreign direct investment is easiest in Pvt Ltd through automatic route for most sectors. Partnership and sole proprietorship are not available to foreigners."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the registration timeline?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Pvt Ltd: 7 to 15 days. OPC: 7 to 15 days. LLP: 10 to 20 days. Partnership: 1 to 7 days. Sole proprietorship: same day with GST and shop act. Timelines depend on MCA processing and state registrar workload. During peak filing season in March and September timelines may extend by 5 to 7 additional days."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do I need a CA for registration?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Not mandatory but strongly recommended. CA or CS ensures correct documentation reduces rejection risk and handles MCA portal complexities. Professional fees range from 3000 for partnership to 15000 for Pvt Ltd. Self-filing is possible but error-prone for first-timers. In India over 90 percent of company registrations are filed through practicing professionals."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is perpetual succession?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Perpetual succession means the company continues to exist regardless of changes in ownership or death of members. Pvt Ltd OPC and LLP have perpetual succession. Partnership dissolves on partner death unless deed says otherwise. This affects business continuity and succession planning."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I change business structure later?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes conversion is possible. Sole proprietorship to Pvt Ltd. Partnership to LLP or Pvt Ltd. OPC to Pvt Ltd. LLP to Pvt Ltd. Each involves specific MCA forms fees and compliance. Plan the right structure from start to avoid conversion costs later."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the cheapest business to start?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Sole proprietorship costs zero to 2000 rupees just GST and shop act registration. Partnership costs 1000 to 5000. These have unlimited liability though. For limited liability the cheapest is LLP at 5000 to 12000. Consider long-term costs not just registration fees."}}]}
</script>
